An ODM official has urged Luhya leaders to forge unity. Speaking in Funyula on Wednesday, Bwiri ODM coordinator Thomas Buluma said lack of unity among the Luhya has divided the community politically.Buluma said without unity, the presidency, which some Luhya leaders have shown interest in, including Bungoma Senator Moses Wetag'ula (pictured) shall remain a mirage. Without unity, Luhyas salivating for the presidency are doomed to fail, he said.